# Sim Plans — Gazebo on the M3PRO Jetson

Execution plan to get a working Gazebo simulation of the ROSMASTER
M3PRO running on the Jetson Orin NX, matching the real robot's ROS 2
topic interface so Project0 code runs unchanged in sim or on hardware.

Scope: **only what is needed to make sim functional.** Polish,
reusable-world library, regression fixtures, and Project0 integration
are out of scope for this file.

Target stack: **Ignition Gazebo Fortress (Gazebo 6)** + `ros_gz` bridge
+ `gz_ros2_control`. This is what the current Humble apt repo ships.
Gazebo Classic is **not** used — the Humble repo has dropped its
Classic bindings (no `ros-humble-gazebo-ros-pkgs`), and new Gazebo is
also where Jazzy/Rolling are headed, so this is the long-term path.

Terminology note: Fortress is the last release using the `ignition::`
C++ namespace and `ign gazebo` binary name; from Harmonic onwards it
becomes `gz::` and `gz sim`. This plan uses the Fortress names
(`ignition::gazebo::systems::*`, `ign gazebo`) because that's what
the binaries on the Jetson expect. ROS-side packages use the newer
`ros-humble-ros-gz-*` / `ros-humble-gz-ros2-control` names.

Package location: **`~/Documents/Projects/m3pro_gazebo/`** on the Mac,
cloned/synced to **`~/m3pro_gazebo_ws/src/m3pro_gazebo/`** on the
Jetson for build + run.

