### S.1 lessons learned (for future reference)

- **Launch argument quoting:** `gz_args:="empty.sdf -r"` gets mangled by
  bash/zsh. Always use single quotes around the whole token:
  `'gz_args:=empty.sdf -r'`. Without the `-r`, Gazebo starts paused and
  you have to press play manually.
- **libEGL / nvidia-drm warnings are benign on this Jetson.** `ros2
  launch` inherits environment variables that cause Mesa to try
  loading an NVIDIA DRI driver from a path that doesn't exist; Mesa
  warns, then falls back to a working renderer. The GUI still opens.
  Do not spend time "fixing" this unless the GUI actually fails to
  open on a future run.
- **Yahboom `yahboom_M3Pro_*` and `M3Pro_*` package name warnings are
  cosmetic.** Those packages use CamelCase which violates ROS 2
  naming rules, so every `ros2 launch` scan prints warnings. Ignore.

