## Known limitations to document up-front (non-goals)

- Mecanum strafe is approximated by diff-drive; sideways motion won't work in sim.
- Servo effort/current in sim does not match real servos; grasp confirmation via effort cannot be validated in sim. Must be validated on hardware.
- Grasp physics for parallel grippers on small objects is unreliable in Gazebo Classic. Sim is for logic validation, not grasp tuning.
- Depth noise model in `gazebo_ros_camera` does not match the Orbbec noise profile; perception tuning against sim depth will not transfer 1:1 to hardware.
- The `arm4_Joiint` URDF typo is preserved, matching the MoveIt config stack on the real robot.

