   `~/yahboomcar_ws/src/yahboom_M3Pro_description/meshes/` into
   `m3pro_gazebo/meshes/`. The sim package owns its own copy so it
   doesn't couple to Yahboom's description package at runtime.
5. Replaced the generated `CMakeLists.txt` with a minimal data-only
   version (just `install(DIRECTORY ... DESTINATION share/${PROJECT_NAME})`).
6. Rewrote `package.xml`: Apache-2.0 license, a real description,
   runtime-only dependencies moved to `exec_depend` (this package
   doesn't need build-time dependencies on anything beyond
   `ament_cmake`), added `ros_gz_image`, `joint_state_broadcaster`,
   `joint_trajectory_controller` since we'll need them at runtime.
7. `colcon build --packages-select m3pro_gazebo` → **succeeds in 1.45 s**.
8. Verified install layout: `install/m3pro_gazebo/share/m3pro_gazebo/`
   contains `urdf/`, `worlds/`, `launch/`, `config/`, `meshes/` (with
   all 20 STL files), plus the standard ROS 2 package hooks.
9. `ros2 pkg prefix m3pro_gazebo` resolves after sourcing the install,
