**Design decisions:**

- **Single-file xacro, no macro library split.** The URDF is small
  enough (~580 lines expanded) that splitting into
  `m3pro_chassis.xacro` / `m3pro_arm.xacro` / `m3pro_sensors.xacro`
  macros would add more overhead than it removes. Revisit if the
  file grows beyond ~1500 lines.
- **`use_sim` arg even though no code gates on it yet.** Declared
  up front so S.4 can add `<xacro:if>` conditional blocks without
  touching the arg boilerplate again. Also documents the design
  intent that the same file must work for both sim and real.
- **Yahboom URDF used as base**, not a hand-rebuild. This preserves
  all the real-world measurements (link origins, joint limits, mesh
  poses, inertial values) and inherits any future Yahboom updates
