**`arm_controllers.yaml`:** `controller_manager` at 100 Hz with
`joint_state_broadcaster`, `arm_controller` (JointTrajectoryController
for the 5 arm joints), and `gripper_controller` (JointTrajectoryController
for `rlink1_Joint` only — `llink1_Joint` follows via ros2_control's
mimic mechanism, not via a separate controller).

**`ros_gz_bridge.yaml`:** 7 bridge entries:
- `/clock` GZ→ROS (so `use_sim_time` works)
- `/cmd_vel` ROS→GZ (Twist)
- `/odom` GZ→ROS (Odometry)
- `/tf` GZ→ROS (Pose_V → TFMessage)
- `/camera/color/image_raw` GZ→ROS (from gz `/camera/image`)
- `/camera/depth/image_raw` GZ→ROS (from gz `/camera/depth_image`)
- `/camera/color/camera_info` GZ→ROS (from gz `/camera/camera_info`)

The ROS-side names deliberately match what the real `orbbec_camera`
driver publishes so downstream perception code doesn't need to
namespace-switch between sim and real.

