| `grep arm4_Joiint` in real expansion | 1 hit (original only, no sim pollution) ✅ |

**Design decisions:**

- **Single `<xacro:if>` gate, not granular gates per plugin.** Cleaner
  diff, one point of control. If we ever need finer gating (e.g.
  "sim without the camera"), we can add sub-args then.
- **Mimic expressed at ros2_control level** rather than editing URDF
  `<mimic>` tags. ros2_control 2.x supports `<param name="mimic">`,
  which means we don't touch the raw joint definitions inherited
  from Yahboom. Cleaner separation; easier to re-sync with upstream
  URDF updates later.
- **No `<gripper_controller>` for `llink1_Joint`** — ros2_control's
  mimic binding handles it for free. Only `rlink1_Joint` is in the
  controller's joint list.
- **Arm and gripper in the SAME `<ros2_control>` system block** (single
  hardware interface) rather than two separate systems. Fewer moving
  parts and matches what `gz_ros2_control` expects.
- **Wheel separation derived from URDF**, not guessed. Explicit formula
  recorded in the sim_plans comments so future maintainers can redo
  it if the chassis URDF changes.
- **Camera clip far = 8.0 m**, not the 4.0 m from the real LiDAR merge
  config. Camera range ≠ laser range. 8 m matches typical Orbbec
  DaBai DCW2 spec and lets sim perception see the bin even when the
  arm is in observation pose.

**Explicit non-goals (left for later steps or dropped):**

- **No `effort` command/state interfaces** on the arm — the real
  servos don't report effort reliably (open item 0.1), and sim
  effort doesn't match real anyway (documented limitation). Stays
  `position`-only until we have real data.
- **No tuning of physics parameters** (friction, damping, etc.).
  Defaults will be used until something misbehaves visibly in S.7.
- **No LiDAR sensor in the URDF yet.** The real robot has 2 × LD-Mini
  Plus LiDARs (confirmed in S.1 summary) but the perception pipeline
  for Project0 Phase 1 only needs the RGBD camera. LiDAR sim can be
  added later without disturbing the arm/camera work.
- **No fine sensor noise modelling.** Sim depth noise doesn't match
  the Orbbec noise profile and tuning perception against sim depth
  will not transfer 1:1 (already flagged in the sim_plans Known
  Limitations section).
- **No sensors system plugin in the URDF.** That plugin is world-
  scoped, not model-scoped. It'll be added to `empty.sdf` /
  `tabletop.sdf` in S.5.

**Not yet tested**: the sim URDF parses, but we haven't spawned the
robot in Gazebo yet. That's S.5/S.7 work. If any plugin filenames,
joint names, or interface mismatches exist, they'll surface during
the verification gate in S.7.

