(default `m3pro`), `x`/`y`/`z` (defaults `0/0/0.05` — 5 cm above
ground so the robot settles rather than clipping).

**Explicit non-goal:** this launch file does NOT start Gazebo. The
top-level `sim.launch.py` in S.6 will start the world, then include
this spawn launch. Keeping them separate lets you iterate on spawn
