### Architecture summary (final state after all fixes)

**Base motion:** `VelocityControl` system plugin (kinematic, in merged
`<gazebo>` block) + `OdometryPublisher` system plugin. ROS `/cmd_vel`
→ `ros_gz_bridge` → GZ `/cmd_vel` → VelocityControl moves model.
GZ `/odom` → bridge → ROS `/odom`.

**Arm + gripper:** `ign_ros2_control/IgnitionSystem` + `gz_ros2_control`
plugin. `joint_state_broadcaster` + `arm_controller`
(JointTrajectoryController, 5 joints) + `gripper_controller`
(JointTrajectoryController, rlink1_Joint). `llink1_Joint` mimics
`rlink1_Joint` at ros2_control level.

**Camera:** SDF `<sensor type="rgbd_camera">` on link DCW2. GZ topics
bridged to real Orbbec names via `ros_gz_bridge.yaml`.

**Physics:** Bullet engine. Sphere wheel collisions. Raised box
base collision. High friction on ground plane. (All of this matters
for arm/gripper physics even though base motion is kinematic.)

**Launch:** `ros2 launch m3pro_gazebo sim.launch.py rviz:=false` with
`ROS_DOMAIN_ID=0`. Launch file auto-unsets FASTRTPS.

